section_a.beneficiaries: Pr Recent advances in artificial intelligence remain hard to access for researchers in life sciences yet promise a great benefit for public good. Artificial Intelligence for Life Sciences CIC aims to unite people interested in combining the two fields in one community. As an organization it will carry out and support research activities on the verge of the two disciplines, as well as, widely disseminate the new knowledge within and outside the community by means of research publication and internet ideas exchange. While doing this, Artificial Intelligence for Life Sciences CIC vows to adhere to the highest ethical and research standards
